                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Ashkenazic semi-cursive script.</summary>
                     <handNote>
                        Copied by four hands. 
                        First hand: <locus from="1v" to="105r">ff. 1v-105r, col. 2, 1. 1</locus>, and <locus from="161r" to="249v">161r-249v</locus>. 
                        Second hand: <locus from="105r" to="133v">ff. 105r, col. 2, 1. 2-133v</locus>, <locus from="143r" to="150v">ff. 143r-150v</locus>, and <locus from="250r" to="270v">ff. 250r-270v</locus>. 
                        Third hand: <locus from="134r" to="142v">ff. 134r-142v</locus>, and <locus from="151r" to="160r">ff. 151r-160r</locus>. 
                        Fourth hand (possibly later):<locus from="271" to="278">last quire (ff. 271-278)</locus>.
                     </handNote>
